13 Voice Actor Profile at Voice Chasers |publisher=Voicechasers.com |date=1969-10-19 |accessdate=2010-01-20}}</ref>|| [[God]], portrayed as a strange, cat-like animal\n| \"[[Are You There God? It's Me, Jesus]]\"<ref name=official2009/>\n|-\n| [[Jesus and Pals|Jesus]]\n| Matt Stone<ref name=\"faq-23apr2002\" /> ||[[Jesus]], who lives in an ordinary house and hosts a [[talk show]] on the local TV station, and is the leader of the Super Best Friends\n| ''[[The Spirit of Christmas (short film)|The Spirit of Christmas]]: Jesus vs. Frosty''\n|-\n| {{sort|Kim, Tuong Lu|[[Tuong Lu Kim]]}}\n| Trey Parker<ref name=\"voicechasers3\"/> || City Wok owner. Was later discovered to be one of many personalities of William Janus, a therapist with Multiple Personality Disorder.\n| \"[[Jared Has Aides]]\"<ref name=official2010>{{cite book|title=The South Park Episode Guide: Seasons 6-10, Volume 2|authors=Sam Stall, James Siciliano, Trey Parker, Matt Stone |publisher=Running Press Book Publishers|year=2010|isbn=9780762438235|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=YWLEQAAACAAJ}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{sort|Maxi, Father|[[Father Maxi]]}}\n| Matt Stone<ref name=\"faq-23apr2002\" /> || [[Catholic priest]]\n| \"[[Mr. Hankey, the Christmas Poo]]\"<ref name=official2009/>\n|-\n| {{sort|McDaniels, Mayor|[[Mayor McDaniels|Mayor Mary McDaniels]]}}\n| Mary Kay Bergman, [[Eliza Schneider]],<ref name=\"autogenerated1\"/> <!-- Mona Marshall,{{fact|date=November 2010}} April Stewart{{fact|date=November 2010}} --> || The Mayor of South Park\n| \"[[Weight Gain 4000]]\"<ref name=official2009/>\n|-\n| {{sort|Mephesto, Alphonse|[[Alphonse Mephisto|Dr. Alphonse Mephesto]]}}\n| Trey Parker<ref name=\"faq-23apr2002\" /> || Local [[mad scientist]] and [[Marlon Brando]] [[lookalike]]\n| \"[[An Elephant Makes Love to a Pig]]\"<ref name=official2009/>\n|-\n| [[List of recurring South Park characters#Moses|Moses]]\n| Trey Parker || A character based on [[Moses]], a gigantic [[dreidel]] who looks and talks like [[List of characters in Tron#Master Control Program and is part of the super best friends|MCP]] from ''[[Tron]]''<ref name=\"faq-5feb2008\">{{cite web |url = http://www.southparkstudios.com/fans/faq/archives.php?month=2&year=2008 |title = FAQ: February 2008 |accessdate = 2009-07-07 |date = 2008-02-05 |publisher = southparkstudios.com }}</ref>\n| \"[[Jewbilee]]\"<ref name=official2009/>\n|-\n| [[Santa Claus (South Park)|Santa]]\n| Trey Parker<ref name=\"faq-23apr2002\" /> || A character based on [[Santa Claus]]\n| ''[[The Spirit of Christmas (short film)|The Spirit of Christmas]]: Jesus vs. Frosty''\n|-\n| {{sort|Slave, Mr.|[[Mr. Slave]]}}\n| [[John Hansen (voice actor)|John Hansen]]<ref name=\"faq-21nov2003\"/>\n| Mr. Garrison's lover and classroom assistant, who later married Big Gay Al\n| \"[[The Death Camp of Tolerance]]\"<ref name=official2009/>\n|-\n| [[List of recurring South Park characters#Starvin' Marvin|Starvin' Marvin]]\n| Trey Parker<ref name=\"faq-23apr2002\" />|| An [[Ethiopia]]n boy\n| \"[[Starvin' Marvin (South Park)|Starvin' Marvin]]\"<ref name=official2009/>\n|-\n| [[Terrance and Phillip]]\n| Matt Stone (Terrance) and Trey Parker (Phillip)<ref name=\"faq-23apr2002\" /> || A Canadian television comedy duo later married to the Queef sisters\n| \"[[Death (South Park)|Death]]\"<ref name=official2009/>\n|-\n| [[Towelie (character)|Towelie]]\n| [[Vernon Chatman]]<ref name=\"faq-23apr2002\" /> || A talking [[recreational drug use|stoner]] [[towel]]; father of Washcloth\n| \"[[Towelie]]\"<ref name=official2009/>\n|-\n| {{sort|Yates, Sergeant Harrison|[[List of recurring South Park characters#Sergeant Harrison Yates|Sergeant Harrison Yates]]}}\n| Trey Parker<ref name=\"premiere1\"/> || A police detective, married to Maggie with an unnamed son\n| \"[[Christian Rock Hard]]\"<ref name=official2009/>\n|-\n| {{sort|Lemmiwinks|[[List of recurring South Park characters#Lemmiwinks|Lemmiwinks]]}}\n| N/A || School [[gerbil]]\n| \"[[The Death Camp of Tolerance]]\"<ref name=official2009/>\n|}\n\n==Former characters==\nA few characters have had a major recurring role in the past episodes in the show before they were either killed or retired.\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable collapsible\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:10%;\"| Character\n! style=\"width:20%;\"| Voiced by\n! class=\"unsortable\" style=\"width:40%;\"| Role\n! style=\"width:15%;\"| First appearance\n! style=\"width:15%;\"| Last appearance\n|-\n| [[Pip Pirrup]]\n| Matt Stone<ref name=\"faq-23apr2002\" /> || The boys' unpopular, stereotypically British classmate, based on the main character in [[Charles Dickens|Dickens']] ''[[Great Expectations]]''. Killed off in \"[[201 (South Park)|201]]\" by Mecha-Streisand.\n| \"[[Cartman Gets an Anal Probe]]\"<ref name=official2009/>\n| \"[[201 (South Park)|201]]\"\n|-\n| [[Chef (South Park)|Chef]]\n| [[Isaac Hayes]],<ref name=\"faq-28jun2001\">{{cite web|url=http://www.southparkstudios.com/fans/faq/archives.php?month=6&year=2001 |title=FAQ: June 2001 |accessdate=2008-10-13 |date=2001-06-28 |publisher=southparkstudios.com |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090410145443/http://www.southparkstudios.com/fans/faq/archives.php?month=6&year=2001 |archivedate=2009-04-10 }}</ref> [[Peter Serafinowicz]] (Darth Chef)<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/profiles/my-secret-life-peter-serafinowicz-actor-and-comedian-age-36-912006.html|title=My Secret Life: Peter Serafinowicz, Actor and comedian, age 36|date=2008-08-30|publisher=[[The Independent]]|accessdate=2009-05-23|last=Philby|first=Charlotte}}</ref> || The school's chef and good friend of the boys, who was killed at the beginning of the [[South Park (season 10)|tenth season]] but was brought back to life as Darth Chef. Despite this, he never appears again after his resurrection.\n| \"[[Cartman Gets an Anal Probe]]\"<ref name=official2009/>\n| \"[[The Return of Chef]]\"\n|-\n| {{sort|Besty Donovan|[[Betsy Donovan]]}}\n| [[April Stewart]]{{Cita