ndance-neon-nabs-police-shooting-drama-monsters-men-1077145|title=Sundance: Neon Nabs Police Shooting Drama 'Monsters and Men'|publisher=|accessdate=January 23, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Border (2018 Swedish film)|Border]]''\n| [[Ali Abbasi (director)|Ali Abbasi]]\n| October 26, 2018\n|Nominated \u2013 [[European Film Award for Best Film]] <br> Nominated \u2013 [[Goya Award for Best European Film]]\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiewire.com/2018/05/neon-border-acquisition-cannes-ali-abbasi-1201962958/|title=NEON Makes First Cannes 2018 Purchase With Ali Abbasi's Acclaimed 'Border'|first=Zack|last=Sharf|date=May 11, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Bodied]]''\n| [[Joseph Kahn]]\n| November 2, 2018\n|\n| <ref>{{Cite web | url=http://collider.com/bodied-joseph-kahn-release-date/ |title = Exclusive: Joseph Kahn's 'Bodied' to Hit Theaters in November Thanks to NEON|date = August 10, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Vox Lux]]''\n| [[Brady Corbet]]\n| December 7, 2018\n|\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/09/neon-vox-lux-natalie-portman-brady-corbet-jude-law-tiff-toronto-international-film-festival-1202462009/|title=As Deadline Told You Today, NEON Closed A Deal On Natalie Portman Music Drama 'Vox Lux' \u2013 Toronto|first=Dino-Ray|last=Ramos|date=September 10, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"14\" | 2019\n| ''[[Apollo 11 (2019 film)|Apollo 11]]''\n| Todd Douglas Miller\n| March 1, 2019\n|[[Critics' Choice Movie Award for Best Documentary Feature]] <br> [[Producers Guild of America Award for Best Documentary Motion Picture]] <br> Nominated \u2013 [[BAFTA Award for Best Documentary]] <br> Nominated \u2013 [[Gotham Independent Film Award for Best Documentary]] <br> Nominated \u2013 [[Independent Spirit Award for Best Documentary Feature]]\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?id=apollo11.htm|title=Apollo 11 (2019)|work=[[Box Office Mojo]]|publisher=[[IMDb]]|accessdate=March 17, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[The Beach Bum]]''\n| [[Harmony Korine]]\n| March 29, 201